# Dependency Policy (依赖管理策略)

Scope: all DTS projects

## General Principles

- Prefer well-maintained, widely-adopted open-source libraries.
- All dependencies must be compatible with offline/air-gapped deployment.
- No SaaS-only dependencies (must work fully self-hosted).
- License whitelist: Apache 2.0, MIT, BSD, MPL 2.0, ISC, PostgreSQL.
- License blacklist: AGPL, SSPL, proprietary (unless explicitly approved).

## Python Banned/Restricted

- No LangChain (use LangGraph directly).
- No pinecone-client (SaaS only).
- No openai SDK as primary (abstract behind LLM provider interface for multi-model support).

## Java Banned/Restricted

- No Spring WebFlux in business CRUD services (use Spring MVC for simplicity).
- No Lombok (use Java records and explicit code).
- No MyBatis (use Spring Data JPA / jOOQ).

## Frontend Banned

- antd, @vanilla-extract/*, styled-components, @iconify/react, apexcharts, date-fns
- Enforced via ESLint no-restricted-imports rule.

## Go Banned/Restricted

- No CGO dependencies in dts-cli (must cross-compile cleanly).

## Version Pinning

- All dependencies must be version-pinned (lock files committed).
- Automated vulnerability scanning (dependabot/renovate) on weekly schedule.
- Critical CVEs must be patched within 48 hours.
